uL\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying Java interface and class structure**\\n\\nI’m considering how in a public test file, you can have top-level package-private interfaces or classes after a public class, without needing dollar signs. Java compiles these into separate .class files, which is good. I want to look at the OverrideCheckTest class and the potential need for failure cases as well. I’m thinking about whether methods like read and write in the parent interface include all inherited methods from superinterfaces, which might not need Object methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring testing interfaces and methods**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how tests might run, though we can’t directly execute them as instructed. I believe that Class.getMethods for an interface returns the public methods from that interface and its superinterfaces, but not from Object. We won't actually run any tests. It might be useful to create an interface that extends a base interface to test inherited methods. Also, should I consider getDeclaredMethods for the parent class? I see that the two call sites branch at the same line.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Psuj9p9WVdI5YfGFFQPK6kRx|fc_0c478813801b729a0169f5540e4a7081a18be6693791ceea2c", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.sf.ehcache/ehcache-core/2.4.4/src/test/java/net_sf_ehcache/ehcache_core/OverrideCheckTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_sf_ehcache.ehcache_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatCode;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatThrownBy;\n\nimport net.sf.ehcache.constructs.nonstop.util.OverrideCheck;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class OverrideCheckTest {\n    @Test\n    void acceptsClassDeclaringAllMethodsRequiredByInterface() {\n        assertThatCode(() -> OverrideCheck.check(TrackedOperations.class, CompleteTrackedOperations.class))\n                .doesNotThrowAnyException();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void reportsMissingMethodOverridesForInterfaceMethods() {\n        assertThatThrownBy(() -> OverrideCheck.check(TrackedOperations.class, IncompleteTrackedOperations.class))\n                .isInstanceOf(RuntimeException.class)\n                .hasMessageContaining(IncompleteTrackedOperations.class.getName())\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"remove(java.lang.Object)\");\n    }\n}\n\ninterface TrackedOperations {\n    Object get(Object key);\n\n    void put(Object key, Object value);\n\n    boolean remove(Object key);\n}\n\nclass CompleteTrackedOperations implements TrackedOperations {\n    @Override\n    public Object get(Object key) {\n        return key;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void put(Object key, Object value) {\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean remove(Object key) {\n        return true;\n    }\n}\n\nclass IncompleteTrackedOperations implements TrackedOperations {\n    @Override\n    public Object get(Object key) {\n        return key;\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public void put(Object key, Object value) {\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public boolean remove(Object key) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"remove is intentionally not supported\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1151, "output": 1035, "cacheRead": 8192, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 10378, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777685503414, "responseId": "resp_0c478813801b729a0169f553ffc35081a1af0a13774d53d389"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Psuj9p9WVdI5YfGFFQPK6kRx|fc_0c478813801b729a0169f5540e4a7081a18be6693791ceea2c", "toolName": "write", "conte